WHENEVER I'VE
THOUGHT ABOUT ME,

12:57.646 --> 12:59.082
IT'S ALWAYS GIL AND ME.

12:59.126 --> 13:01.476
I DREAM ABOUT BEING
IN A RELATIONSHIP AGAIN.

13:01.519 --> 13:02.782
I EVEN DREAM ABOUT

13:02.825 --> 13:05.480
BEING BACK TOGETHER WITH GIL
AGAIN SOMETIMES.

13:05.523 --> 13:07.830
DON'T WORRY, I GET OVER
THAT ONE REAL FAST.

13:07.874 --> 13:09.571
BUT THE TRUTH IS, I'M NOT
READY TO START DATING.

13:09.614 --> 13:11.486
I'M NOT EVEN INTERESTED.

13:11.529 --> 13:13.096
- WHICH IS EXACTLY
WHEN GOD MIGHT SNEAK UP

13:13.140 --> 13:15.011
AND TAKE YOU BY SURPRISE.

13:15.055 --> 13:18.798
YOU SEE, GOD HAS A PLAN
FOR EACH OF US,

13:18.841 --> 13:22.105
AND YOU HAVE TO BE OPEN
TO WHATEVER HE SENDS YOU,

13:22.149 --> 13:23.803
WHETHER YOU THINK YOU'RE
READY FOR IT OR NOT.

13:23.846 --> 13:26.806
OH, AND BY THE WAY,

13:26.849 --> 13:30.200
JARED CALLED HIS FATHER
TODAY AND LEFT A MESSAGE.

13:30.244 --> 13:32.246
OF COURSE, GIL NEVER
CALLED HIM BACK.

13:32.289 --> 13:35.118
OH. JARED!

13:35.162 --> 13:36.511
JARED, DINNER'S READY.

13:39.557 --> 13:41.559
- HEY, LANNY, WHAT ARE YOU,
ABOUT TEN YEARS OLD

13:41.603 --> 13:42.865
WHEN YOU'RE IN
THE FOURTH GRADE?

13:42.909 --> 13:45.128
- ABOUT THAT. WHY?
- THAT LETTER I GOT TODAY,

13:45.172 --> 13:47.739
IT WAS A "DEAR G.I" LETTER
FROM A KID IN ROWENSFIELD.

13:47.783 --> 13:49.654
ISN'T ROWENSFIELD
NEAR FORT SEBASTIAN?

13:49.698 --> 13:51.265
- YOU NEED TO GET OFF
THE BASE A LITTLE MORE.

13:51.308 --> 13:53.180
IT'S ABOUT 25 MILES
DOWN THE INTERSTATE.

13:53.223 --> 13:55.660
- I GOTTA TELL YOU,
THAT LETTER REALLY HIT HOME.

13:55.704 --> 13:57.140
REMINDED ME
OF WHEN I WAS A KID.

13:57.184 --> 13:58.750
- BEEN THERE, DONE THAT?- GOT THE T-SHIRT TO PROVE IT.

13:58.794 --> 14:00.622
- [laughs]

14:00.665 --> 14:02.058
- DO YOU MIND IF I BORROW
THAT PAPER AND PEN?

14:02.102 --> 14:03.886
- WHAT, ARE YOU GONNA
WRITE HIM BACK?

14:03.930 --> 14:06.628
- I WISH I HAD SOMEONE WRITE
WHEN I WAS HIS AGE.

14:06.671 --> 14:08.978
THANK YOU.
- KNOCK YOURSELF OUT.

14:12.242 --> 14:15.550
- "DEAR JARED, IT WAS REAL NICETO GET YOUR LETTER,

14:15.593 --> 14:17.639
"AND AWFUL NICE
OF YOU TO WRITE.

14:17.682 --> 14:19.293
"YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
HOW OLD YOU ARE.

14:19.336 --> 14:20.772
"BUT YOU'RE IN
THE FOURTH GRADE,

14:20.816 --> 14:23.732
"SO I GUESS
YOU'RE ABOUT TEN.

14:23.775 --> 14:25.647
"YOU'RE RIGHT ABOUT
IT'S TOUGH GROWING UP

14:25.690 --> 14:26.430
IN A DIFFERENT PLACE
THAN YOUR DAD."

14:29.738 --> 14:32.567
- BUT THE VERSION OF PROTEAN CADTHEY'RE USING IS 6.2.

14:32.610 --> 14:34.569
THE LAST ONE I USED
WAS 2.7.

14:34.612 --> 14:38.660
- [laughs] I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

14:38.703 --> 14:39.879
- THAT MEANS
I'M TEN YEARS OUT OF DATE.

14:39.922 --> 14:41.706
- WELL, YOU KNEW THAT
GOING IN.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.621
YOU'LL GET UP TO SPEED.

14:43.665 --> 14:44.884
- MOM, EVERYONE IS TEN YEARS
YOUNGER THAN ME.

14:44.927 --> 14:48.322
- SO? THEY'LL TAKE A BREAK,
HAVE KIDS,

14:48.365 --> 14:50.106
AND BE THE SAME AGE
YOU ARE.

14:50.150 --> 14:52.848
- THE MEN TOO?
- YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

14:52.892 --> 14:54.850
- YEAH, WELL, I HAVE TO WORK ONESATURDAY OUT OF THE MONTH.

14:54.894 --> 14:56.765
THEY DIDN'T BOTHER TELLING METHAT DURING THE INTERVIEW.

14:56.808 --> 14:58.332
I MEAN, WHAT AM I GONNA DO
WITH JARED?

14:58.375 --> 14:59.855
HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY FRIENDS.I CAN'T SET UP ANY PLAYDATES.

14:59.899 --> 15:01.683
- WELL, I'LL TAKE CARE
OF HIM.

15:01.726 --> 15:04.773
WE CAN HAVE SOME
QUALITY BONDING TIME.

15:04.816 --> 15:10.039
LOOK, THE WAY I SEE IT,
YOU HAVE JUST HAD

15:10.083 --> 15:14.739
YOUR FIRST DAY BACK AT WORK
IN TEN YEARS AND SURVIVED.

15:14.783 --> 15:16.741
NOW QUIT UNDERESTIMATING
YOURSELF.

15:16.785 --> 15:18.656
- BUT MOM--

15:18.700 --> 15:20.745
- BUT YOU DO INTEND TO GO BACKTOMORROW, DON'T YOU?

15:20.789 --> 15:22.617
- YES.
- WELL, THEN THAT

15:22.660 --> 15:24.706
IS THE ONLY BUT
THAT COUNTS.

15:24.749 --> 15:27.317
JARED, YOU'VE GOT SOME MAIL
ON THE TABLE.

15:27.361 --> 15:31.756
- IS IT FROM DAD?- ONLY IF HE JOINED THE ARMY.

15:31.800 --> 15:34.237
- IT'S FROM THAT SOLDIER
I WROTE TO.

15:36.936 --> 15:40.243
- "DEAR JARED, IT WAS REAL NICETO GET YOUR LETTER,

15:40.287 --> 15:42.637
"AND AWFUL NICE
OF YOU TO WRITE.

15:42.680 --> 15:44.726
"YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
HOW OLD YOU ARE.

15:44.769 --> 15:45.945
"BUT YOU'RE IN
THE FOURTH GRADE,

15:45.988 --> 15:48.860
"SO I GUESS
YOU'RE ABOUT TEN.

15:48.904 --> 15:50.340
"YOU'RE RIGHT ABOUT
IT'S TOUGH GROWING UP

15:50.384 --> 15:52.995
"IN A DIFFERENT PLACE
THAN YOUR DAD. I KNOW.

15:53.039 --> 15:55.998
"I WAS YOUR AGE WHEN MY DAD
LEFT MY MOM AND WE MOVED.

15:56.042 --> 15:58.740
"I REMEMBER THINKING,'I'LL NEVER MAKE NEW FRIENDS.

15:58.783 --> 16:00.394
"NOT GOOD ONES
LIKE I HAD BEFORE.'

16:00.437 --> 16:03.614
BUT YOU KNOW SOMETHING?
I DID."

16:09.316 --> 16:11.622
[overlapping chatter]

16:20.240 --> 16:25.288
[cheers and laughter]

16:32.295 --> 16:34.341
- THERE HE IS,
THERE HE IS!

16:34.384 --> 16:39.041
[overlapping chatter]

17:02.804 --> 17:04.022
- JUST THE MAN
I WAS LOOKING FOR.

17:04.066 --> 17:06.938
- HEY, WHAT UP, MAN?

17:06.982 --> 17:08.810
- LAST CHANCE TO COME DOWN
TO SAN DIEGO WITH US.

17:08.853 --> 17:10.724
- THANKS, BUT NO THANKS.
I'M ALL RIGHT.

17:10.768 --> 17:12.291
- COME ON, VINCE.
YOU'RE ON LEAVE.

17:12.335 --> 17:14.337
- YOU CAN'T SPEND IT ALONE
ON THE BASE.

17:14.381 --> 17:16.731
- MAN, I LIKE THE BASE
WHEN IT'S EMPTY.

17:16.773 --> 17:19.167
- YOU'VE BEEN DIVORCED
THREE YEARS, RIGHT?

17:19.212 --> 17:21.953
COME ON, LIZ GOT A WHOLE LISTOF WOMEN TO FIX YOU UP WITH.

17:21.997 --> 17:23.259
- THE LAST THING I NEED
IN MY LIFE

17:23.303 --> 17:24.955
IS A WOMAN RIGHT NOW.

17:25.000 --> 17:26.480
THE ARMY AND WOMEN
DON'T MIX WITH ME,

17:26.522 --> 17:29.048
ESPECIALLY WHEN
WE'RE OVERSEAS.

17:29.091 --> 17:32.051
- THREE YEARS.
- I APPRECIATE IT.

17:32.094 --> 17:34.879
- ALL RIGHT,
YOU KNOW WHAT? I GIVE UP.

17:34.923 --> 17:37.012
I SAW THE MAIL CLERK PUT
A LETTER IN YOUR BOX.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.970
IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND,
GIVE ME A CALL.

17:39.014 --> 17:40.494
- I WILL.

17:40.537 --> 17:41.886
HAVE FUN.

17:41.930 --> 17:45.412
[grunting]

17:45.455 --> 17:46.891
- "DEAR SERGEANT CARRERA,

17:46.935 --> 17:48.980
"MY MOM SAYS I HAVE TO PLAY
BASEBALL.

17:49.024 --> 17:50.286
"SHE SAYS IT WILL
HELP ME MAKE FRIENDS,

17:50.330 --> 17:51.461
"BUT WHO WANTS TO BE FRIENDS
WITH THE KID

17:51.505 --> 17:52.810
"WHO THROWS LIKE A GIRL?

17:52.854 --> 17:54.464
"WE HAD TRYOUTS ON MONDAY.

17:54.508 --> 17:56.901
"I WAS TERRIBLE.
I COULDN'T HIT THE BALL.

17:56.945 --> 17:58.773
"I WAS THE SLOWEST KID
ON THE FIELD.

17:58.816 --> 18:00.340
"I HAVEN'T MADE
ANY FRIENDS YET,

18:00.383 --> 18:02.342
"AND I DON'T THINK
I'LL BE PLAYING BASEBALL.

18:02.385 --> 18:04.126
"MAYBE I SHOULD JUST
FORGET IT.

18:04.170 --> 18:06.259
"ANYWAY, I HOPE EVERYTHING
IS GOOD OVER THERE.

18:06.302 --> 18:08.522
"WE ARE THINKING ABOUT YOU
AND HOPE YOU ARE HOME SOON.

18:08.565 --> 18:10.915
YOUR FRIEND,
JARED MARSHALL."

18:21.143 --> 18:24.015
- DEAR JARED, I GOT
YOUR LETTER ABOUT BASEBALL.

18:24.059 --> 18:25.800
YOUR MOM'S RIGHT.

18:25.843 --> 18:27.541
IT'S A GREAT WAY
TO MAKE FRIENDS.

18:27.584 --> 18:30.631
THE KEY...

18:47.604 --> 18:49.432
- JARED, I'M HOME.

18:54.611 --> 18:56.222
[doorbell rings]

18:56.265 --> 18:57.266
- [sighs]

18:59.399 --> 19:00.965
- CAN I HELP YOU?
- YES, MA'AM.

19:01.009 --> 19:02.445
DOES JARED MARSHALL
LIVE HERE?

19:02.489 --> 19:04.491
- YES.
- I'M VINCE CARRERA.

19:04.534 --> 19:06.014
UH, THE SOLDIER
HE'S BEEN WRITING TO.

19:06.057 --> 19:07.581
- OH, MY GOODNESS.
[laughs]

19:07.624 --> 19:09.626
IT'S SO NICE TO MEET YOU.

19:12.629 --> 19:15.110
WELL, YOU MUST BE
JARED'S MOM.

19:15.154 --> 19:18.200
- YES, I AM.

19:18.244 --> 19:21.029
- WELL, IF THE LETTERS SAY
ANYTHING ABOUT YOUR BOY,

19:21.072 --> 19:24.163
HE'S QUITE THE YOUNG MAN.
- THANK YOU.

19:24.206 --> 19:27.601
- YOU KNOW, I AM SO SORRY
TO BARGE IN LIKE THIS.

19:27.644 --> 19:29.429
I'LL BE ON MY WAY.

19:29.472 --> 19:31.866
- YOU KNOW, I JUST--I THOUGHTYOU WERE IN BOSNIA.

19:31.909 --> 19:35.130
- OH, I WAS. I GOT BACK
A COUPLE DAYS AGO.

19:35.174 --> 19:39.003
I'M STATIONED UP
AT FORT SEBASTIAN. IT'S--

19:39.047 --> 19:41.136
IT'S ABOUT 25 MILES
UP THE INTERSTATE.

19:41.180 --> 19:43.965
- I'M DANA.

19:44.008 --> 19:47.186
- UM, HI, MRS. MARSHALL.
- OH, DANA.

19:47.229 --> 19:49.057
- OKAY.

19:49.100 --> 19:50.972
- JARED IS REALLY GONNA
WANT TO MEET YOU.

19:51.015 --> 19:52.103
HE'S GONNA BE SO EXCITED.

19:52.147 --> 19:52.974
WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR ONE SECOND?

19:53.017 --> 19:54.454
- SURE.
- SORRY.

19:54.497 --> 19:56.630
- IT'S OKAY. I GOT IT.
- OH, SORRY. [laughs]

19:56.673 --> 20:00.895
JARED. JARED.
HEY, JARED, COME HERE QUICK.

20:00.938 --> 20:01.939
THERE'S SOMEONE
WHO WANTS TO MEET YOU.

20:01.983 --> 20:04.551
HURRY.

20:04.594 --> 20:07.945
COME ON, LET'S GO.

20:07.989 --> 20:11.210
JARED, UH, THIS IS
SERGEANT VINCE CARRERA,

20:11.253 --> 20:12.907
THE SOLDIER YOU'VE BEEN
WRITING TO.

20:12.950 --> 20:14.038
HE'S HOME FROM BOSNIA.

20:14.082 --> 20:17.085
- NICE TO MEET YOU
IN PERSON, JARED.

20:17.128 --> 20:18.913
HEY, REMEMBER
THAT LAST LETTER,

20:18.956 --> 20:20.654
HOW YOU WERE SAYING YOU
WERE HAVING A HARD TIME

20:20.697 --> 20:22.917
GETTING STARTED
WITH BASEBALL?

20:22.960 --> 20:25.659
WELL, BESIDES BEING
A PRETTY GOOD SOLDIER,

20:25.702 --> 20:29.053
I'M PRETTY GOOD
AT BASEBALL TOO.

20:29.097 --> 20:31.491
AND I WAS HOPING THAT,
UH, OF COURSE,

20:31.534 --> 20:33.014
IF IT'S OKAY WITH YOUR MOM,

20:33.057 --> 20:35.190
THAT I GET TO COACH YOU
A LITTLE BIT.

20:35.234 --> 20:40.021
- PLEASE, MOM, PLEASE?

20:40.064 --> 20:41.675
- AND MOM
WOULD HAVE TO COME,

20:41.718 --> 20:44.547
BECAUSE WE NEED FIELDERS,
RIGHT?

20:44.591 --> 20:47.463
- WELL, HOW COULD I REFUSE?

20:47.507 --> 20:50.727
- ALL RIGHT, LET'S PLAY
SOME BASEBALL.

21:01.564 --> 21:03.566
ALL RIGHT, JARED.

21:03.610 --> 21:05.133
YOU KNOW ONE OF THE MOSTIMPORTANT THINGS ABOUT BASEBALL?

21:05.176 --> 21:06.700
- NO.
- IT'S FUN. COME ON.

21:06.743 --> 21:08.484
LET'S GO.

21:08.528 --> 21:11.095
THAT'S IT.
YOU READY?

21:11.139 --> 21:12.227
GET THAT.

21:12.271 --> 21:15.099
THROW IT BACK.

21:15.143 --> 21:17.537
WOW.
WOW, ALL RIGHT.

21:17.580 --> 21:19.016
JUST GET IN FRONT OF THE BALLLIKE YOU'RE DOING, ALL RIGHT?

21:22.368 --> 21:25.109
NICE, MAN.

21:25.153 --> 21:26.807
NICE CATCH, MAN.

21:35.772 --> 21:37.339
OH, WOW, MAN.

21:41.343 --> 21:43.127
WELL, YOU'VE GOT A GOOD,
NATURAL EYE FOR CATCHING,

21:43.171 --> 21:44.999
THAT'S FOR SURE.YOUR HITTING'S ALL RIGHT TOO.

21:45.042 --> 21:47.001
NOW YOUR THROWING,
WE'LL WORK ON.

21:47.044 --> 21:49.264
YOU KNOW, WHEN I FIRST
STARTED PLAYING BASEBALL

21:49.308 --> 21:51.527
WHEN I WAS A KID,
I WASN'T MUCH GOOD.

21:51.571 --> 21:53.616
BUT LIKE YOU,
I COULD CATCH,

21:53.660 --> 21:56.097
SO I BECAME A CATCHER.

21:56.140 --> 21:57.316
THAT WAY, WHEN I LEARNED
HOW TO THROW,

21:57.359 --> 21:59.100
I COULD STILL
HELP MY TEAM OUT.

21:59.143 --> 22:01.145
DO YOU KNOW IF THEY PICKED
A CATCHER FOR THE TEAM YET?

22:01.189 --> 22:03.191
- I THINK THEY'RE GONNA DECIDEAFTER THE FIRST PRACTICE.

22:03.234 --> 22:04.801
- WELL, ALL RIGHT.
LET'S MAKE YOU A CATCHER.

22:08.370 --> 22:09.676
PITCH TO ME.

22:09.719 --> 22:13.375
- OH. [laughs]
- COME ON.

22:13.419 --> 22:14.768
ALL RIGHT, YOU READY?
- I'M GONNA STAND HERE.

22:14.811 --> 22:16.335
- FIRST THINGS FIRST.

22:16.378 --> 22:18.554
FEET SHOULDER-WIDTH,

22:18.598 --> 22:20.121
SQUARIN' THEM UP
WITH YOUR BODY, ALL RIGHT?

22:20.164 --> 22:22.036
- YEAH.
- GET DOWN THERE,

22:22.079 --> 22:23.211
CROUCHED DOWN.
- I CROUCH?

22:23.254 --> 22:25.779
- GIVE THE PITCHER
A BIG OLD TARGET.

22:25.822 --> 22:27.650
- JARED, WATCH OUT.

22:30.131 --> 22:31.350
- AH.

22:31.393 --> 22:33.047
THE KEY TO CATCHING,

22:33.090 --> 22:34.353
ALWAYS GET
IN FRONT OF THE BALL.

22:34.396 --> 22:35.745
YOU DON'T WANT TO LET IT GET
TO THE BACKSTOP,

22:35.789 --> 22:37.138
ALL RIGHT?
'CAUSE THEY'LL STEAL A BASE.

22:37.181 --> 22:38.357
YOU READY TO TRY IT?
- YEAH.

22:38.400 --> 22:41.098
- ALL RIGHT,
GET OVER THERE.

22:41.142 --> 22:43.623
THAT'S IT.
GOOD.

22:43.666 --> 22:45.102
WAY TO MEASURE IT UP.

22:45.146 --> 22:48.062
- THEN CROUCH AND TARGET.

22:48.105 --> 22:49.629
- LOOK AT YOU.YOU'RE A CATCHER ALREADY, MAN.

22:49.672 --> 22:52.719
- [laughs]

22:52.762 --> 22:54.938
- NICE THROW, LADY.

22:57.637 --> 22:58.812
ALL RIGHT, YOU READY?

22:58.855 --> 22:59.682
- YEAH.
- IT'S COMING AT YOU.

23:02.293 --> 23:04.252
ALL RIGHT, WAY TO STAY
IN FRONT OF THE BALL.

23:04.295 --> 23:06.385
THAT WAS GOOD.

23:06.428 --> 23:08.430
WELL, WE'LL WORK ON THAT.

23:10.345 --> 23:12.086
ALL RIGHT, WAY TO GET
IN FRONT OF THE BALL.

23:12.129 --> 23:14.393
THAT'S WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

23:14.436 --> 23:16.133
- SO WERE YOU GOOD AT BASEBALLWHEN YOU WERE YOUNG?

23:16.177 --> 23:18.353
- WHOA, MAN,
YOU SAYIN' I'M OLD?

23:18.397 --> 23:20.834
- NO, YOU'RE NOT OLD OLD.
YOU'RE LIKE, UM,

23:20.877 --> 23:22.662
OLD LIKE, UM,
MY MOM'S OLD.

23:22.705 --> 23:24.228
- WHOA, WAIT A MINUTE.

23:24.272 --> 23:25.316
ARE YOU SAYING
THAT I'M OLD?

23:25.360 --> 23:26.840
- NO, YOU'RE NOT OLD.
YOU'RE--

23:26.883 --> 23:29.190
NO, I DIDN'T MEAN IT.
UHH!

23:29.233 --> 23:30.844
- IT'S OKAY.
WE KNOW WHAT YOU MEANT.

23:30.887 --> 23:32.802
[laughs]

23:32.846 --> 23:34.282
- SO WERE YOU GOOD
AT BASEBALL?

23:34.325 --> 23:35.501
- I WAS PRETTY GOOD
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

23:35.544 --> 23:37.328
I HAD LOADS OF FUN,
I'LL TELL YOU THAT.

23:37.372 --> 23:38.852
- WILL YOU COME
TO COACH ME AGAIN?

23:38.895 --> 23:41.463
- OH, JARED,
I AM SURE THAT, UH,

23:41.507 --> 23:43.639
SERGEANT CARRERA HAS, UH,
A LOT OF OTHER THINGS

23:43.683 --> 23:45.380
HE NEEDS TO BE DOING.

23:45.424 --> 23:47.338
- ACTUALLY, MY BATTALION'S
ON LEAVE RIGHT NOW,

23:47.382 --> 23:49.732
SO I HAVE NOTHING BUT TIME.

23:49.776 --> 23:53.301
I'D LOVE TO COACH JARED AGAIN,IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT WITH YOU.

23:53.344 --> 23:55.782
- WELL, THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

23:55.825 --> 23:57.697
WHY DON'T WE WAIT AND SEE HOWHE DOES AT HIS NEXT PRACTICE?

23:57.740 --> 24:00.439
- ALL RIGHT.
JUST LET ME KNOW.

24:00.482 --> 24:01.744
NOW YOU PROMISE
YOU'RE GONNA ASK THE COACH

24:01.788 --> 24:03.354
ABOUT THE CATCHER,
RIGHT?

24:03.398 --> 24:06.793
- YES, SIR,
SERGEANT--VINCE.

24:06.836 --> 24:08.751
- THANK YOU.

24:08.795 --> 24:10.623
IT WAS NICE MEETING YOU.

24:10.666 --> 24:13.234
- LIKEWISE, MA'AM.

24:13.277 --> 24:14.453
DANA.

24:14.496 --> 24:17.107
LIKEWISE.

24:37.737 --> 24:40.348
- HE HAS GOOGLED
EVERY CATCHER

24:40.391 --> 24:43.525
SINCE ABNER DOUBLEDAY
INVENTED THE GAME.

24:43.569 --> 24:46.310
THAT SERGEANT REALLY LEFT
A BIG IMPRESSION ON JARED.

24:46.354 --> 24:48.704
- I COULD HAVE NEVER TAUGHT HIMEVERYTHING HE TAUGHT HIM.

24:48.748 --> 24:50.924
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN HOW PATIENTHE WAS WITH JARED.

24:50.967 --> 24:53.187
HE WAS TOTALLY THERE
JUST FOR HIM.

24:53.230 --> 24:55.406
- GOD WORKS
IN MYSTERIOUS WAYS.

24:55.450 --> 24:56.756
IS HE CUTE?

24:56.799 --> 24:58.714
- I DIDN'T NOTICE.

24:58.758 --> 25:00.934
- I KNOW,
BUT IF YOU HAD NOTICED.

25:00.977 --> 25:02.718
- YES, YOU WOULD SAY
HE WAS CUTE,

25:02.762 --> 25:04.241
AND I AM NOT READY
TO THINK ABOUT THAT.

25:07.767 --> 25:10.944
- OKAY, YOU GUYS,
ARE YOU READY?

25:10.987 --> 25:13.337
- GO ON.

25:16.863 --> 25:18.473
ASK HIM.

25:18.517 --> 25:20.301
- ASK ME WHAT?

25:20.344 --> 25:22.782
- CAN I TRY OUT
FOR CATCHER, PLEASE?

25:22.825 --> 25:24.392
- HAVE YOU EVER
SUITED UP BEFORE?

25:24.435 --> 25:26.525
- NO, BUT SERGEANT CARRERA SAYSI'M GOOD AT CATCHING.

25:26.568 --> 25:29.571
- AND WHO IS
SERGEANT CARRERA?

25:29.615 --> 25:30.920
IT DOESN'T MATTER. SURE YOU
CAN TRY OUT FOR CATCHER.

25:30.964 --> 25:32.400
SUIT UP,
AND YOU CAN DO IT

25:32.443 --> 25:33.967
WHILE THE OTHERS
HAVE BATTING PRACTICE.

25:34.010 --> 25:35.490
GO ON.
COME ON, EVERYBODY.

25:35.534 --> 25:38.232
TAKE THE FIELD.
LET'S GO.

25:38.275 --> 25:39.842
BATTING PRACTICE.

25:42.323 --> 25:44.194
YOU'RE UP.
YOU'RE ON DECK.

25:46.588 --> 25:48.068
GOOD CATCH, JARED.

25:52.420 --> 25:55.423
[overlapping chatter]

25:55.466 --> 25:56.293
- WHOO! GOOD ONE!

26:00.689 --> 26:02.343
[phone rings]

26:02.386 --> 26:04.563
- OH, WOULD YOU ANSWER THAT?
- OH, SURE.

26:04.606 --> 26:06.303
HELLO.

26:06.347 --> 26:07.435
- IS THIS
JARED MARSHALL'S MOTHER?

26:07.478 --> 26:09.916
- YES, IT IS.
- THIS IS COACH HANLEY.

26:09.959 --> 26:11.395
I'M JUST LETTING YOU KNOW

26:11.439 --> 26:13.354
THAT JARED WILL BE PLAYING
FOR THE CHARGERS.

26:13.397 --> 26:15.399
- IS HE THE CATCHER?
- DEFINITELY.

26:15.443 --> 26:18.446
- YES!
THANK YOU SO MUCH!

26:18.489 --> 26:20.535
YOU ARE THE CATCHER
FOR THE CHARGERS!

26:20.579 --> 26:22.537
- YES!
- WHOO!

26:22.581 --> 26:24.931
- BINGO!
- [laughs]

26:24.974 --> 26:26.889
- YAY!
- YES!

26:26.933 --> 26:30.284
- YOU READY TO DO THIS?

26:30.327 --> 26:31.677
UHH! HERE WE GO.
YOU READY?

26:31.720 --> 26:33.548
ALL RIGHT.

26:33.592 --> 26:35.506
- HEY, WE'RE GOING OUT
FOR HAMBURGERS AFTER THIS.

26:35.550 --> 26:37.900
DO YOU WANT TO COME?
- OH, UH, JARED,

26:37.944 --> 26:39.641
VINCE HAS SPENT MOST OF
THE AFTERNOON WITH US.

26:39.685 --> 26:42.426
I THINK THAT WE SHOULD QUIT
WHILE WE'RE AHEAD.

26:42.470 --> 26:45.429
- PLEASE, MOM?
- WELL, IT'S NOT UP TO ME,

26:45.473 --> 26:46.909
BUT IF YOU WOULD LIKE
TO JOIN US,

26:46.953 --> 26:49.477
YOU'D BE MORE THAN WELCOME.

26:49.520 --> 26:50.957
- YOU KNOW, I WOULDN'T MIND
JOINING YOU,

26:51.000 --> 26:53.350
ON ONE CONDITION.

26:53.394 --> 26:54.351
MY TREAT.

26:54.395 --> 26:56.615
- OH, NO, WE--
WE COULDN'T.

26:56.658 --> 27:00.706
- I DON'T THINK
I COULD MAKE IT THEN.

27:00.749 --> 27:03.317
- OKAY, AT TIMES LIKE THIS,
MY MOTHER TAUGHT ME

27:03.360 --> 27:06.059
TO GIVE IN GRACIOUSLY
AND SAY THANK YOU.

27:06.102 --> 27:08.452
- MY PLEASURE.

27:08.496 --> 27:09.932
SO DID YOU GET
YOUR CATCHER'S GEAR YET?

27:09.976 --> 27:12.326
- MM, HE GETS IT
NEXT WEEK.

27:12.369 --> 27:13.632
THE TEAM SUPPLIES IT
THIS YEAR,

27:13.675 --> 27:14.850
AND THEN WE HAVE TO BUY IT
FOR HIM NEXT YEAR.

27:14.894 --> 27:15.938
- OH, THAT MEANS
HE'S GONNA GIVE YOU

27:15.982 --> 27:17.418
A NEW CATCHER'S MITT.

27:17.461 --> 27:19.072
IT'S GONNA BE ALL STIFF
AS A BOARD.

27:19.115 --> 27:20.464
I THOUGHT ABOUT THAT,
THOUGH.

27:20.508 --> 27:23.032
SO I GOT YOU THIS.

27:23.076 --> 27:23.990
IT'S WHAT THEY USE
IN THE MAJORS.

27:24.033 --> 27:25.513
SOFTEN THAT MITT
RIGHT UP.

27:25.556 --> 27:27.515
- WOW.

27:27.558 --> 27:30.431
- WHAT DO YOU SAY, JARED?
- THANKS.

27:30.474 --> 27:32.085
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

27:32.128 --> 27:36.393
- THAT WAS REALLY
THOUGHTFUL OF YOU.

27:36.437 --> 27:37.873
YOU KNOW, I GOT THE FEELING
THAT WHEN YOU SAID

27:37.917 --> 27:39.092
YOU HAD A LOT OF FUN PLAYING
BASEBALL IN HIGH SCHOOL

27:39.135 --> 27:42.008
THAT YOU WERE BEING MODEST.

27:42.051 --> 27:45.054
- WELL, I WAS OFFERED A TRIPLE-ACONTRACT OUT OF HIGH SCHOOL,

27:45.098 --> 27:47.535
BUT YOU KNOW, ALL I EVER WANTEDTO DO WAS BE IN THE ARMY,

27:47.578 --> 27:50.494
SO I DIDN'T SIGN IT.

27:50.538 --> 27:51.670
PLUS I COULDN'T
HIT A CURVE BALL,

27:51.713 --> 27:52.932
SO THE MAJOR LEAGUES
WERE A LONG-SHOT.

27:52.975 --> 27:54.847
- YOU COULD HAVE GONE PRO.

27:59.068 --> 28:01.636
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP
AT THIS HOUR?

28:01.680 --> 28:03.986
- I'M JUST TRYING TO MAKE SENSEOF SOME NEW SOFTWARE,

28:04.030 --> 28:05.466
CAD SOFTWARE THEY USE
AT THE OFFICE.

28:05.509 --> 28:07.990
- I CAN'T HELP YOU THERE.

28:08.034 --> 28:11.385
IT TOOK ME THREE WHOLE NIGHT
COURSES AT COMMUNITY COLLEGE

28:11.428 --> 28:12.560
JUST TO LEARN HOW TO EMAIL
AND GOOGLE.

28:12.603 --> 28:14.518
[laughs]

28:14.562 --> 28:16.433
- OH, I JUST--
I FEEL SO OVERWHELMED.

28:16.477 --> 28:17.696
EVERYTHING'S CHANGED
SO MUCH.

28:17.739 --> 28:19.567
I'M AFRAID I'M NEVER
GOING TO CATCH UP.

28:19.610 --> 28:21.569
AND I'M ON PROBATION UNTIL
MY FIRST EVALUATION.

28:21.612 --> 28:23.136
- AND THEN THEY WILL REALIZE

28:23.179 --> 28:25.486
HOW LUCKY THEY ARE
TO HAVE YOU.

28:25.529 --> 28:28.402
- I KNOW. I KNOW THAT I AM
37 YEARS OLD,

28:28.445 --> 28:30.143
BUT I FEEL LIKE I AM SEVEN,
AND I WOULD LIKE YOU

28:30.186 --> 28:33.146
TO WAVE YOUR MAGIC MOM WAND

28:33.189 --> 28:34.669
LIKE YOU DID
WHEN I WAS A CHILD

28:34.713 --> 28:36.018
AND MAKE EVERYTHING OKAY
AGAIN.

28:36.062 --> 28:38.455
- THE NICE THING
ABOUT GROWING UP

28:38.499 --> 28:40.153
IS THAT YOU GET TO WAVE
YOUR OWN WAND.

28:40.196 --> 28:42.111
YOU'RE WORKING HARD ENOUGH.

28:42.155 --> 28:46.594
ALL YOU NEED IS SOME FAITH
IN YOURSELF.

28:46.637 --> 28:48.509
[laughs]

28:48.552 --> 28:52.731
MMM.
THAT POPCORN SMELLS GOOD.

28:52.774 --> 28:54.558
- OH, IT'S SO GOOD.

28:54.602 --> 28:55.995
- MMM.
- [laughs]

28:56.038 --> 28:58.040
I'M GONNA HAVE
SOME OF THAT.

29:01.740 --> 29:02.784
- HEY, VINCE.
- YO.

29:02.828 --> 29:04.786
- HOLD UP.

