- LET ME ASK YOU
A QUESTION.

29:36.818 --> 29:39.734
WHAT PART OF "I'M NOT LOOKING"DID YOU NOT GET?

29:39.778 --> 29:41.649
- THE "N"? NO, NO, NO.
IT WAS THE "O," RIGHT?

29:41.692 --> 29:43.477
MAYBE THE "T"?

29:43.520 --> 29:45.696
NOW I'M NOT LOOKING,
I'M NOT INTERESTED.

29:45.740 --> 29:46.654
BUT TELL LIZ THANKS
ANYWAY, ALL RIGHT?

29:46.697 --> 29:49.135
- YOU GOT IT.
[laughs]

29:51.746 --> 29:54.618
- OH, JARED, LOOK.

29:54.662 --> 29:56.664
- HEY.
- HI.

29:56.707 --> 29:59.493
VINCE, THIS IS MY MOM,
LOUISE METCALF.

29:59.536 --> 30:01.582
MOM, THIS IS
SERGEANT VINCE CARRERA.

30:01.625 --> 30:03.192
- A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU,
MA'AM.

30:03.236 --> 30:05.020
- WELL, IT'S A PLEASURE
TO MEET YOU TOO.

30:05.064 --> 30:06.979
MY GRANDSON TELLS ME

30:07.022 --> 30:10.112
THAT YOU ARE ABLE TO LEAP TALLBUILDINGS IN A SINGLE BOUND.

30:10.156 --> 30:12.158
- OH, YEAH?
WELL, ONLY SMALL ONES.

30:12.201 --> 30:14.073
NOTHING OVER 20 STORIES.

30:14.116 --> 30:15.291
[laughter]
ARE YOU READY, BUD?

30:15.335 --> 30:16.249
- YES, SIR.
- ALL RIGHT, GRAB THIS BAT.

30:16.292 --> 30:18.207
LET'S GO PLAY.

30:21.167 --> 30:23.909
- I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU SAY.
HE IS CUTE.

30:23.952 --> 30:26.520
- MOM.
- WELL.

30:26.563 --> 30:28.565
I'M JUST TRYING,
YOU KNOW.

30:28.609 --> 30:31.699
- ALL RIGHT, WATCH THE BALLRIGHT INTO THE BAT, ALL RIGHT?

30:31.742 --> 30:34.049
- HEY, OUR FIRST GAME IS THIS
WEDNESDAY. WILL YOU COME?

30:34.093 --> 30:36.486
- YOU CAN COUNT ON IT.

30:40.664 --> 30:41.665
- EACH AND EVERY
PIECE OF EQUIPMENT

30:41.709 --> 30:43.145
YOUR PLATOONS
ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR

30:43.189 --> 30:45.104
MUST BE THOROUGHLY
EXAMINED,

30:45.147 --> 30:46.670
AND ALL DAMAGE AND/OR
LOSS THAT OCCURS

30:46.714 --> 30:48.542
WHILE THEY ARE IN TRANSIT
MUST BE REPORTED

30:48.585 --> 30:51.632
TO THE QM ON THE 2404s
WITHIN 14 DAYS

30:51.675 --> 30:53.286
OF THE BATTALION RETURNING
FROM LOCKLEIGH.

30:53.329 --> 30:54.809
BUT WHEN THOSE 14 DAYS
ARE UP,

30:54.853 --> 30:56.855
YOU NEED TO GET ON THAT.

30:56.898 --> 30:58.160
OKAY.

31:12.261 --> 31:14.263
- HIS CAR'S NOT HERE.

31:14.307 --> 31:16.787
- OH, YE OF LITTLE FAITH.

31:16.831 --> 31:20.008
VINCE WILL BE HERE.
HE'S A MAN OF HIS WORD.

31:29.713 --> 31:30.845
- I'M LEAVING THIS
TO THE FIRE TEAM.

31:30.889 --> 31:31.977
THE LEADER
IS BILL'S LEADERSHIP.

31:32.020 --> 31:33.892
- [exhales]

31:33.935 --> 31:35.850
- SO...

31:35.894 --> 31:37.330
- THAT KID I'VE BEEN COACHINGIN BASEBALL,

31:37.373 --> 31:38.331
HIS FIRST GAME
IS AT 15:30 HOURS.

31:38.374 --> 31:40.246
- SHOOT.

31:40.289 --> 31:41.595
WELL, IS HIS MOM
GONNA BE THERE?

31:41.638 --> 31:44.206
- MM-HMM.
- SO THIS IS A DATE.

31:44.250 --> 31:45.468
- IT AIN'T A DATE.

31:48.210 --> 31:49.777
- SERGEANT MAJOR.
- YES, SERGEANT.

31:49.820 --> 31:51.257
- SERGEANT CARRERA
WOULD LIKE TO KNOW

31:51.300 --> 31:52.345
HOW MUCH LONGER
THIS IS GOING TO TAKE

31:52.388 --> 31:53.868
BECAUSE HE HAS A DATE.

31:53.912 --> 31:55.609
[laughter]

31:55.652 --> 31:57.611
- YOU'RE GOING
ON A DATE, SERGEANT?

31:57.654 --> 31:59.352
- NO, SERGEANT MAJOR,
IT'S MORE LIKE WE--

31:59.395 --> 32:01.180
[laughter and chatter]

32:01.223 --> 32:03.617
- LET'S GO, LET'S GO.

32:03.660 --> 32:05.619
[laughter and chatter]

32:05.662 --> 32:08.883
- YOU CAN GO, MAN.
YOU CAN GO.

32:08.927 --> 32:10.711
- LET'S GO!

32:10.754 --> 32:12.887
- MOM, IT'S OKAY
IF VINCE DOESN'T COME.

32:12.931 --> 32:15.368
I MEAN, SOMETIMES MEN CAN'T DOTHINGS THEY SAID THEY WOULD

32:15.411 --> 32:17.196
BECAUSE THEY'RE BUSY
AT WORK.

32:17.239 --> 32:21.940
- WELL, LOOK WHO'S HERE.

32:21.983 --> 32:23.463
WHAT DID I SAY?

32:25.334 --> 32:28.207
- HEY.
- WHEW! SORRY I'M LATE.

32:28.250 --> 32:30.383
I GOT HELD UP
AT A MEETING.

32:30.426 --> 32:31.862
- WHAT'S UP?
- GO GET 'EM!

32:31.906 --> 32:33.386
- [laughs]
THANK YOU FOR BEING HERE.

32:33.429 --> 32:34.778
- I TOLD YOU
I'D SHOW UP.

32:36.432 --> 32:38.652
GO GET 'EM, BUD!

32:38.695 --> 32:41.437
[cheers and applause]

32:49.837 --> 32:52.361
- HOW LONG BEFORE JARED
COMES UP TO BAT AGAIN?

32:52.405 --> 32:53.754
- OH, I THINK HE'S UP FIFTH.

32:53.797 --> 32:55.277
- I FEEL LIKE
AN ICE CREAM CONE.

32:55.321 --> 32:56.887
HOW ABOUT THE TWO OF YOU?

32:56.931 --> 32:59.673
- OOH, I WOULD LOVE
A VANILLA CONE.

32:59.716 --> 33:01.196
- GOOD, GOOD.
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

33:01.240 --> 33:02.241
LET ME GET THAT.
- NO, NO, NO.

33:02.284 --> 33:03.851
YOU SIT DOWN.
THIS IS MY TREAT.

33:03.894 --> 33:05.331
- YEAH, DON'T ARGUE WITH HER.YOU WON'T WIN.

33:05.374 --> 33:07.246
- OKAY. IN THAT CASE, I'LL TAKEA VANILLA CONE TOO.

33:07.289 --> 33:10.423
- YOU'VE GOT IT.
- THANK YOU.

33:10.466 --> 33:12.729
- GOOD LUCK, JARED.

33:12.773 --> 33:14.731
[laughs]

33:14.775 --> 33:16.690
I HAVE TO THANK YOU FOREVERYTHING YOU'VE DONE FOR HIM.

33:16.733 --> 33:18.953
YOU'VE MADE
SUCH A BIG DIFFERENCE.

33:18.997 --> 33:20.302
- OH, PLEASE, I AM HAVING
SUCH A GOOD TIME.

33:22.304 --> 33:25.220
[overlapping chatter]

33:25.264 --> 33:27.831
- MAMA'S PROUD.
YEAH, MAMA'S PROUD!

33:27.875 --> 33:28.963
- LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

33:29.007 --> 33:30.008
[cheering]

33:30.051 --> 33:31.835
- NICE.

33:31.879 --> 33:34.316
COME ON, COME ON,
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING!

33:34.360 --> 33:36.840
- IT'S HARD TO GROW UP
WITH AN ABSENTEE DAD.

33:36.884 --> 33:38.799
- YEAH, FLORIDA'S
A LONG WAY AWAY.

33:38.842 --> 33:41.280
- YEAH, WELL, GIL WASN'T ANYCLOSER WHEN HE LIVED WITH US.

33:41.323 --> 33:42.846
- I KNOW HOW THAT FEELS.

33:42.890 --> 33:44.848
SEE, MY DADDY
WORKED ON OIL RIGS

33:44.892 --> 33:48.765
AND NOT MUCH ROOM FOR A FAMILYON THOSE THINGS.

33:48.809 --> 33:51.116
AND THEN WHEN HE WASN'T
ON THE RIG,

33:51.159 --> 33:53.988
WELL, YOU KNOW, HOME WAS THE
LAST PLACE HE WANTED TO BE.

33:54.032 --> 33:55.903
IT WAS LIKE ME AND MY MOM
WEREN'T EVEN THERE.

33:55.946 --> 33:57.948
HE WAS JUST MARKIN' TIME
TO GET BACK OUT THERE.

33:57.992 --> 34:00.081
YOU KNOW, MOM TRIED.

34:00.125 --> 34:01.909
SHE WOULD MOVE US AROUND
EVERY COUPLE YEARS,

34:01.952 --> 34:03.824
FIND SOMEPLACE THAT YOU COULDHOPEFULLY SETTLE DOWN,

34:03.867 --> 34:07.088
BUT NOT SO MUCH.

34:08.829 --> 34:13.051
OH, OKAY, OKAY.

34:13.094 --> 34:14.487
NICE, NICE!

34:14.530 --> 34:16.793
- HAVE YOU EVER
BEEN MARRIED?

34:16.837 --> 34:18.447
- ONCE.

34:18.491 --> 34:19.882
YOU KNOW,
FOR SOME REASON,

34:19.927 --> 34:21.320
I JUST COULDN'T--

34:21.362 --> 34:23.016
I COULDN'T FIGURE OUT
HOW TO TAKE CARE OF HER

34:23.061 --> 34:24.975
WHEN I WAS OVERSEAS.

34:25.018 --> 34:29.197
SO SHE FOUND SOMEONE
TO TAKE CARE OF HER.

34:30.893 --> 34:32.809
- I'M SORRY.
- NO, DON'T BE.

34:32.853 --> 34:34.072
IT WAS, LIKE,
THREE YEARS AGO.

34:34.114 --> 34:35.725
I'M SO OVER THAT.

34:38.554 --> 34:39.947
[cheering]

34:39.989 --> 34:42.949
NICE CUT, THOUGH.
NICE CUT.

34:42.993 --> 34:45.909
- LET'S GO!

34:45.953 --> 34:47.389
- HOW LONG SINCE
YOU'VE BEEN DIVORCED?

34:47.433 --> 34:49.087
- UM, ME?
ABOUT A YEAR.

34:49.130 --> 34:51.393
- STILL A LITTLE RAW?

34:51.437 --> 34:54.527
- NO. NOT NOW.
- HMM.

34:54.570 --> 34:56.572
[applause]
- NICE THROW. GOOD JOB.

34:59.053 --> 35:02.056
- SO NOW I'M WORKING ON
BEING A SINGLE MOM

35:02.100 --> 35:04.189
AND WHAT I WANT TO DO
WITH THE REST OF MY LIFE.

35:04.232 --> 35:05.973
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

35:06.016 --> 35:08.845
YOU ARE DOING A DARN GOOD JOBWITH JARED.

35:08.889 --> 35:11.413
IF YOU DO HALF AS GOOD
A JOB ON YOURSELF,

35:11.457 --> 35:12.849
YOU'RE GONNA BE JUST FINE,
DANA.

35:12.893 --> 35:16.288
- HEY, BATTER, BATTER!
HEY, BATTER!

35:16.331 --> 35:17.898
