35:17.941 --> 35:19.465
- OH, I'M SORRY.
[laughs]

35:21.989 --> 35:24.774
- GOOD EYE. GOOD EYE, JARED.
GOOD EYE, JARED.

35:27.603 --> 35:29.562
YOU PLAYED A GOOD GAME
TODAY, BUD.

35:29.605 --> 35:32.521
- I STRUCK OUT TWICE.
- YOU WERE ONE FOR THREE.

35:32.565 --> 35:34.001
THAT'S
A 3.33 BATTING AVERAGE.

35:34.044 --> 35:35.394
MOST PROS DON'T DO
THAT WELL.

35:35.437 --> 35:37.178
- WE STILL LOST.

35:37.222 --> 35:38.353
- YOU KNOW THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN A GOOD PLAYER

35:38.397 --> 35:39.528
AND A GREAT PLAYER?

35:39.572 --> 35:43.532
HOW QUICK THEY BOUNCE BACK,
ALL RIGHT?

35:43.576 --> 35:47.188
HEY, UM, THIS SATURDAY,
IS GUEST DAY AT THE BASE,

35:47.232 --> 35:49.582
AND I WAS HOPING THAT Y'ALL
COULD BE MY GUESTS.

35:49.625 --> 35:51.888
- CAN WE, PLEASE?

35:51.932 --> 35:53.368
- UM, YOU KNOW,
THAT SOUNDS REALLY NICE,

35:53.412 --> 35:55.153
BUT IT'S THIS SATURDAY?
- YEAH.

35:55.196 --> 35:56.980
- I'M WORKING THIS SATURDAY.
- OH, ALL RIGHT.

35:57.024 --> 35:58.373
- MOM, PLEASE.

35:58.417 --> 36:00.245
- HONEY, I'M NEW
AT THIS COMPANY,

36:00.288 --> 36:02.856
AND I CAN'T GO CHANGING THINGSLIKE THAT JUST YET.

36:02.899 --> 36:06.076
- WELL, I COULD TAKE HIM.
- YES!

36:06.120 --> 36:07.687
- ALL RIGHT.

36:10.907 --> 36:13.606
- HEY, DANA.
- YES, SIR.

36:13.649 --> 36:15.564
- I, UH, TOOK A LOOK
AT THE PLANS

36:15.608 --> 36:17.871
YOU DID FOR THE GENERAL
ARCHITECT PEOPLE.

36:17.914 --> 36:20.090
IT'S GOOD STUFF.
- THANK YOU.

36:20.134 --> 36:22.180
- ARE YOU STILL ON
YOUR TRIAL PERIOD WITH US?

36:22.223 --> 36:24.921
- YES.
- NOT NOW.

36:24.965 --> 36:25.661
FROM NOW ON,
YOU'RE PERMANENT.

36:27.663 --> 36:29.491
- [laughs]

36:30.971 --> 36:34.409
