WE'VE GOT TO GET GOING!

48:53.017 --> 48:56.629
OH, HEY, ARE YOU ALMOST READY?WE'VE GOT TO GO.

48:56.672 --> 48:58.631
- HE HAS A VERY BAD
UPSET STOMACH.

48:58.674 --> 49:01.764
- OH, NO, WHERE DOES IT HURT?- EVERYWHERE.

49:01.808 --> 49:02.635
- IT MUST HAVE BEEN
SOMETHING HE ATE

49:02.678 --> 49:04.637
OR SOME KIND OF A BUG.

49:04.680 --> 49:06.726
- IT DOESN'T MATTER.

49:06.769 --> 49:08.380
I'LL JUST CALL VINCE AND
TELL HIM WE CAN'T MAKE IT.

49:08.423 --> 49:10.164
- NO, MOM,
YOU'VE GOT TO GO.

49:10.208 --> 49:12.210
- HONEY, I HAVE TO STAY HERE
AND TAKE CARE OF YOU.

49:12.253 --> 49:13.298
- WHY CAN'T GRANDMA?

49:13.341 --> 49:14.821
- WELL, GRANDMA'S GOING OUT.

49:14.864 --> 49:16.692
- NO, HER MEETING
GOT CANCELED.

49:16.736 --> 49:18.956
YOU CAN'T LET VINCE DOWN.

49:18.999 --> 49:21.610
- OKAY, I'LL GO.

49:24.831 --> 49:26.659
- OH!

49:26.702 --> 49:27.790
- OOH, THAT'S GOOD.
- [laughs]

49:27.834 --> 49:30.924
- OH, YEAH.
- OH, WOW. [laughs]

49:30.968 --> 49:34.275
- UM, I'M REAL SORRY JARED
WASN'T FEELING WELL.

49:34.319 --> 49:37.061
HE WOULD HAVE LOVED THIS.
- OH, HE WOULD HAVE.

49:37.104 --> 49:39.889
BUT I'VE FORGOTTEN HOW NICE
IT IS TO HAVE ADULT TIME.

49:39.933 --> 49:41.935
WELL, WITH SOMEONE
OTHER THAN MY MOTHER.

49:41.979 --> 49:44.024
[both laugh]

49:44.068 --> 49:45.417
YOU KNOW, THIS IS THE FIRST
NIGHT I'VE BEEN OUT

49:45.460 --> 49:47.375
WITHOUT JARED
IN ALMOST A YEAR.

49:47.419 --> 49:50.291
- HOW DOES IT FEEL?
- GOOD.

49:50.335 --> 49:52.250
REALLY GOOD.
- ALL RIGHT.

49:52.293 --> 49:55.688
- [laughs]

49:55.731 --> 49:57.298
- DO YOU REMEMBER
THAT MOROCCAN RESTAURANT

49:57.342 --> 50:00.301
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT?

50:00.345 --> 50:02.434
DO YOU WANT TO HAVE DINNER THEREWITH ME SOMETIME?

50:02.477 --> 50:05.002
- ARE YOU ASKING ME OUT
ON A DATE?

50:05.045 --> 50:06.916
- I THINK I AM.

50:06.960 --> 50:08.440
- A DATE DATE?

50:08.483 --> 50:10.050
- MM-HMM.

50:11.791 --> 50:13.967
OUR FIRST DATE.

50:14.011 --> 50:17.101
- WELL, WHEN SHOULD WE GO
ON THIS DATE?

50:17.144 --> 50:19.451
- TUESDAY.

50:19.494 --> 50:21.931
- WHAT TIME?

50:21.975 --> 50:23.455
- 8:00.

50:23.498 --> 50:25.892
- OH, NO.

50:25.935 --> 50:28.764
SOME THINGS ARE JUST
GONNA HAVE TO WAIT

50:28.808 --> 50:31.332
UNTIL OUR DATE AT 8:00
ON TUESDAY.

50:34.335 --> 50:37.817
- IT'S ABOUT TIME.

50:37.860 --> 50:40.428
WELL, WHAT MADE YOU
FINALLY SEE SENSE?

50:40.472 --> 50:42.474
- WELL, I THINK BECAUSE THERE'SA BUILT-IN ENDING.

50:42.517 --> 50:45.042
EVENTUALLY,
HE'LL SHIP OUT

50:45.085 --> 50:46.826
AND IT'LL BE OVER.
DOES THAT SOUND TERRIBLE?

50:46.869 --> 50:49.829
- NO, NOT AT ALL.

50:49.872 --> 50:52.092
ANYWAY, WHO CARES WHAT HAPPENSTWO MONTHS FROM NOW?

50:52.136 --> 50:55.400
THE IMPORTANT THING IS THAT
YOU ARE GOING OUT ON A DATE.

50:55.443 --> 51:00.405
OOH, THANK YOU.
- [laughs] YEAH.

51:04.887 --> 51:07.107
- WHAT'S THIS?
- IT'S COLOGNE LIZ BUYS ME.

51:07.151 --> 51:09.414
SHE SAYS WEAR IT, BUT DON'T
USE AS MUCH AS I DO.

51:09.457 --> 51:10.893
- [laughs]

51:10.937 --> 51:12.504
- IF YOU IRON THE CREASE
ONE MORE TIME,

51:12.547 --> 51:14.375
YOU'RE GONNA CUT YOURSELF
ON IT.

51:14.419 --> 51:15.985
SO YOU READY TO TAKE
THE PLUNGE, HUH?

51:16.029 --> 51:17.509
- LIVING TODAY TODAY.

51:17.552 --> 51:19.293
MAN, I FINALLY GOT

51:19.337 --> 51:20.164
THAT YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT TOMORROW.

51:20.207 --> 51:21.817
THANKS, LANNY.

51:21.861 --> 51:22.688
- HEY, THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS
ARE FOR.

51:22.731 --> 51:24.516
YOU GOTTA LIVE
IN THE MOMENT.

51:24.559 --> 51:26.083
- MAN, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M DOING.

51:26.126 --> 51:28.911
I'M SERIOUS, MAN.
I WAS RUDE THE OTHER NIGHT.

51:28.955 --> 51:30.826
I'M SO CLUMSY.
I TRIED TO KISS HER, MAN.

51:30.870 --> 51:32.350
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT I'M SO STUPID.

51:32.393 --> 51:34.352
- LOOK, SHE'S STILL
GOING OUT WITH YOU, RIGHT?

51:34.395 --> 51:36.049
- WELL, YEAH.
- OKAY.

51:36.093 --> 51:38.530
'CAUSE LOOK, DATING IS LIKE
RIDING A BIKE.

51:38.573 --> 51:39.966
YOU WOBBLE A BIT
WHEN YOU FIRST GET BACK ON,

51:40.009 --> 51:41.794
BUT YOU NEVER FORGET HOW.

51:41.837 --> 51:43.100
- MAN, I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT A BIKE LOOKS LIKE.

51:43.143 --> 51:44.536
- LOOK, WILL YOU QUIT
IRONING THOSE PANTS

51:44.579 --> 51:45.537
AND GET INTO 'EM?

51:45.580 --> 51:46.886
OR YOU'RE GONNA BE LATE,

51:46.929 --> 51:47.887
AND THAT'S WAY TOO BIT
OF A WOBBLE

51:47.930 --> 51:49.106
FOR A FIRST DATE.
- OH, HEY.

51:49.149 --> 51:50.107
YOU'RE WRINKLING THEM.
- PUT 'EM ON.

51:50.150 --> 51:52.413
- ALL RIGHT.

51:59.899 --> 52:03.032
- SO?
- IT'S FABULOUS, AGAIN.

52:03.076 --> 52:04.904
- I LIKED THE ONE BEFORE
THE LAST ONE BETTER.

52:04.947 --> 52:06.384
- NO, YOU'RE GOING
OUT TO DINNER.

52:06.427 --> 52:09.126
THIS ONE HAS MORE, UM,
BREATHING ROOM.

52:09.169 --> 52:10.866
[both laugh]

52:10.910 --> 52:12.346
- YOU MUST LIKE HIM
AN AWFUL LOT

52:12.390 --> 52:14.087
IF YOU'RE MAKING THIS MUCH FUSSABOUT WHAT YOU WEAR.

52:14.131 --> 52:16.045
- YOU KNOW, I DO HAVE
ANOTHER OPTION.

52:16.089 --> 52:18.091
I HAVE A SKIRT
AND A REALLY CUTE BLOUSE.

52:18.135 --> 52:20.137
[doorbell rings]

52:20.180 --> 52:22.400
- TOO LATE NOW.WHAT YOU SEE IS WHAT YOU GET.

52:22.443 --> 52:25.359
AND YOU LOOK--
- DY-NO-MITE!

52:25.403 --> 52:26.882
- UHH!
- [laughs]

52:26.926 --> 52:29.624
THANK YOU.
I'LL GET THE DOOR.

52:35.456 --> 52:37.066
- YOU LOOK NICE.

52:37.110 --> 52:41.419
- YOU LOOK...STUNNING.

52:41.462 --> 52:42.724
- THANK YOU.

52:46.511 --> 52:49.470
- ARE THOSE FOR ME?
- OH!

52:49.514 --> 52:52.169
YEAH. I'M SORRY.

52:52.212 --> 52:54.388
- THANK YOU.
[sniffs]

52:54.432 --> 52:55.259
- HEY, VINCE.
- HEY, BUD.

52:55.302 --> 52:56.912
- HEY.

52:56.956 --> 53:00.220
- WOW, THESE ARE
REALLY BEAUTIFUL.

53:00.264 --> 53:02.048
HEY, WILL YOU DO ME A FAVOR
AND PUT THESE IN WATER?

53:02.091 --> 53:03.963
AND MAKE SURE YOU LISTEN
TO GRANDMA

53:04.006 --> 53:05.182
AND THAT YOU ARE IN BED
BY 9:00.

53:05.225 --> 53:06.444
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

53:06.487 --> 53:08.141
- MWAH.
- HAVE FUN.

53:08.185 --> 53:10.448
- I LOVE YOU.

53:10.491 --> 53:11.884
- BYE, BUD.
- BYE.

53:15.670 --> 53:16.932
- [chuckles softly]

53:16.976 --> 53:18.630
- I THINK HE'LL BE GOOD
FOR HER.

53:18.673 --> 53:21.676
- [laughs]
SO DO I.

53:23.069 --> 53:27.073
[chatter]

53:27.116 --> 53:32.470
- THE COUSCOUS WITH VEGETABLESAND CHICKEN.

53:32.513 --> 53:34.211
- WHAT WAS THAT DISH
THAT COMES WITH...

53:34.254 --> 53:35.647
- WOW, IT ALL SOUNDS
SO GOOD.

53:35.690 --> 53:37.126
WHAT DO YOU RECOMMEND?

53:37.170 --> 53:39.172
- WHAT DO YOU FEEL LIKE?
- I HAVE NO IDEA.

53:39.216 --> 53:40.913
[laughs]
- OKAY.

53:40.956 --> 53:42.567
UM, HOW ABOUT I ORDERFOR BOTH OF US AND WE'LL SHARE?

53:42.610 --> 53:44.090
- PLEASE.
- OKAY.

53:44.133 --> 53:45.483
WE'LL START WITH THE HARIRA
WITH DATES.

53:45.526 --> 53:46.919
THAT'S A SOUP.

53:46.962 --> 53:48.529
AND THEN THE METZI,
THE MATCHUI,

53:48.573 --> 53:50.096
AND THE CHICKEN
WITH THE TATCHOUKA.

53:50.139 --> 53:52.316
AND A LITTLE COUSCOUS.
THANK YOU.

53:52.359 --> 53:54.056
- ARE YOU ORDERING ENOUGH
TO FEED THE WHOLE BATTALION?

53:54.100 --> 53:57.103
- NO, JUST THE PLATOON.
- [laughs]

53:57.146 --> 53:58.974
WHAT?

53:59.018 --> 54:01.499
- OH.

54:01.542 --> 54:02.630
YOU JUST LOOK
REALLY BEAUTIFUL.

54:05.242 --> 54:08.549
SO TELL ME EVERYTHING
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU.

54:08.593 --> 54:10.072
- EVERYTHING?
- YEAH.

54:10.116 --> 54:11.117
I WANT TO KNOW
ALL YOUR SECRETS.

54:11.160 --> 54:13.162
[both laugh]

54:13.206 --> 54:14.686
- OH, DO YOU KNOW
HOW LONG IT'S BEEN

54:14.729 --> 54:16.253
SINCE I'VE BEEN
ON A DATE?

54:16.296 --> 54:19.517
ALMOST 14 YEARS.
- WOW.

54:19.560 --> 54:21.954
LIZ TRIED TO SET ME UP
ON A BLIND DATE

54:21.997 --> 54:23.172
WHEN ME AND MY EX
JUST SPLIT UP.

54:23.216 --> 54:26.088
I WAS SO NOT READY.
I CHICKENED OUT.

54:26.132 --> 54:27.960
- I WAS SO NERVOUS ABOUT GOINGON MY FIRST DATE.

54:28.003 --> 54:30.963
- SO WAS I.

54:31.006 --> 54:32.051
THANKS FOR MAKING IT
SO EASY.

54:32.094 --> 54:35.054
- OH, I'M HAVING
SO MUCH FUN.

54:35.097 --> 54:37.404
- GOOD.

54:39.580 --> 54:43.541
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

54:43.584 --> 54:46.544
SHOULD WE DO THIS AGAIN?

54:46.587 --> 54:49.155
- OH, YOU MEAN, UH,
JUST THE TWO OF US

54:49.198 --> 54:51.636
GO ON A DATE?
- YEAH.

54:51.679 --> 54:56.162
- HEY, UM...

54:56.205 --> 54:59.252
WHERE DOES JARED FIT
INTO ALL OF THIS?

54:59.296 --> 55:01.559
- WHAT JARED AND I HAVE,
IT'S--IT'S SEPARATE.

55:01.602 --> 55:03.082
I MEAN, HE'S MY BUDDY.

55:03.125 --> 55:04.605
I'M GONNA BE THERE
FOR JARED

55:04.649 --> 55:08.348
AS LONG AS HE NEEDS ME,
OKAY?

55:08.392 --> 55:11.699
- AND WHAT HAPPENS TO US
WHEN YOU GO OVERSEAS AGAIN?

55:11.743 --> 55:14.049
- HEY, DANA, THAT'S--
THAT'S--

55:14.093 --> 55:17.531
THAT'S MONTHS AWAY.
I MEAN...

55:17.575 --> 55:19.881
LET'S JUMP OFF THAT BRIDGEWHEN WE GET TO IT, ALL RIGHT?

55:22.275 --> 55:25.147
- FOR NOW, WE'LL TAKE IT
ONE DATE AT A TIME.

55:25.191 --> 55:27.628
- ONE DATE AT A TIME.

55:27.672 --> 55:29.978
I LIKE THE WAY THAT SOUNDS.
- GOOD.

55:32.198 --> 55:35.157
THEN YES, I THINK WE SHOULD
DO THIS AGAIN.

55:58.746 --> 56:00.748
[overlapping chatter]

56:05.840 --> 56:08.103
- SO?

56:08.147 --> 56:10.802
- SO WHAT?

56:10.845 --> 56:12.369
- HOW DID IT GO?

56:12.412 --> 56:15.241
- IT WENT OKAY.

56:15.284 --> 56:18.113
- HOW OKAY? ARE YOU
GONNA SEE HER AGAIN?

56:18.157 --> 56:19.680
- OH, YEAH, I'M GONNA
SEE HER AGAIN.

56:19.724 --> 56:21.813
AT JARED'S BASEBALL GAME.

56:21.856 --> 56:23.075
- LOOK, QUIT DODGING
THE QUESTION.

56:23.118 --> 56:24.337
ARE YOU GONNA
SEE HER AGAIN?

56:24.381 --> 56:27.253
- YEAH, MAN, I'M GONNA
SEE HER AGAIN.

56:27.296 --> 56:29.255
WE'RE GOING OUT
TOGETHER.

56:29.298 --> 56:30.691
- ALL RIGHT.
NOW SHE'S THE ONLY GIRL

56:30.735 --> 56:32.127
YOU WANT TO SEE
AT THE MOMENT, RIGHT?

56:32.171 --> 56:34.216
'CAUSE IF NOT,
SINCE YOU'RE DATING,

56:34.260 --> 56:35.130
YOU'RE GONNA BE GOING
ON BLIND DATES

56:35.174 --> 56:36.697
FROM NOW UNTIL CHRISTMAS.

56:36.741 --> 56:38.395
- SHE'S THE ONLY ONE
I WANT TO SEE.

56:38.438 --> 56:40.135
- ALL RIGHT, GOOD.

56:40.179 --> 56:41.398
NOW SINCE YOU TWO
ARE DATING,

56:41.441 --> 56:43.269
YOU ARE DOUBLE DATING
WITH US FRIDAY NIGHT.

56:43.312 --> 56:44.444
NO EXCUSES.

56:44.488 --> 56:45.750
- OKAY.

56:45.793 --> 56:47.055
[grunts, exhales]

56:50.276 --> 56:53.366
- HEY, SLEEPYHEAD.
- SO, HOW DID IT GO?

56:53.410 --> 56:54.628
- HOW DID WHAT GO?

56:54.672 --> 56:56.108
WELL, WE ATE
MIDDLE-EASTERN FOOD

56:56.151 --> 56:57.631
AND IT WAS DELICIOUS.

56:57.675 --> 56:59.285
- AND?
- AND WHAT?

56:59.328 --> 57:00.721
- DO YOU LIKE HIM,
YOU KNOW, LIKE THAT?

57:00.765 --> 57:02.114
IS HE YOUR BOYFRIEND?

57:02.157 --> 57:04.116
- OKAY, THAT IS NOT
AN APPROPRIATE QUESTION

57:04.159 --> 57:05.378
FOR A SON TO ASK
HIS MOTHER,

57:05.422 --> 57:06.553
ESPECIALLY
MY TEN-YEAR-OLD SON.

57:06.597 --> 57:08.468
- UH, JARED,

57:08.512 --> 57:10.383
UH, TAKE YOUR BREAKFAST
INTO THE LIVING ROOM.

57:10.427 --> 57:12.559
[laughs]

57:12.603 --> 57:14.692
SO, HOW DID IT GO?

57:14.735 --> 57:16.258
- IT WAS GREAT.

57:16.302 --> 57:18.130
AND WE AGREED THAT
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

57:18.173 --> 57:19.784
VINCE AND JARED
WILL BE BUDDIES.

57:19.827 --> 57:23.657
- AND DO YOU LIKE HIM?
YOU KNOW, LIKE THAT?

57:23.701 --> 57:25.877
- YEAH, I-I THINK I DO.

57:25.920 --> 57:28.227
I MEAN, IT'S SCARY,
BUT YEAH.

57:28.270 --> 57:29.533
- GOOD.

57:29.576 --> 57:31.317
IT'S ABOUT TIME

57:31.360 --> 57:33.275
YOU GOT THAT PART OF YOUR HEARTWORKING AGAIN.

57:33.319 --> 57:36.104
[mouthing words]

57:40.326 --> 57:41.936
- HANG ON, DANA!

57:46.332 --> 57:48.290
- THERE YOU GO!
[laughs]

57:51.816 --> 57:54.427
- OH, YEAH.
- WHOO!

57:54.471 --> 57:56.908
OH, MAN!

57:56.951 --> 57:58.736
- WHOO, THAT WAS FUN.
[laughter]

57:58.779 --> 58:00.781
THERE YOU GO.
CHAMP!

58:00.825 --> 58:02.522
- THAT WAS A LOT OF FUN.

58:02.566 --> 58:04.829
BOY, OH, BOY, I AM GONNA BE
STIFF TOMORROW.

58:04.872 --> 58:06.831
- YOU ARE.
- [laughs]

58:06.874 --> 58:08.876
- THANK YOU.
- THANK YOU.

58:08.920 --> 58:10.225
- THANK YOU.
- HEY, LIZ.

58:10.269 --> 58:12.314
YOU GOT ONE FOR ME?
- OF COURSE.

58:12.358 --> 58:13.577
- HEY, DANA, YOU KNOW CATHY?
CATHY, DANA.

58:13.620 --> 58:15.404
- HI.
- HI.

58:15.448 --> 58:16.318
- CATHY'S MARRIEDTO JOSH BORGUNNER OVER THERE.

58:16.362 --> 58:17.755
- AH.

58:17.798 --> 58:19.191
- SO DO YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA HAVE?

58:19.234 --> 58:21.367
A GIRL OR A BOY?
- NOPE, AND I DON'T WANT TO.

58:21.410 --> 58:23.804
AS LONG AS HE OR SHE'S
GOT TWO GOOD ARMS

58:23.848 --> 58:25.937
AND TWO GOOD LEGS AND FIVE
FINGERS AND FIVE TOES

58:25.980 --> 58:27.416
ON EACH SIDE, I DON'T CARE
WHAT'S IN THE MIDDLE.

58:27.460 --> 58:28.896
- THAT'S RIGHT.

58:28.940 --> 58:32.204
- SO WHEN ARE YOU DUE?
- JULY.

58:32.247 --> 58:36.251
- WELL, LET'S HOPE
THAT THEY'LL BE HOME THEN.

58:36.295 --> 58:38.210
- WHAT DO YOU WANT
ON YOUR BURGER, BABY?

58:38.253 --> 58:39.690
- I'VE BEEN MARRIED TO HIM
FOR 15 YEARS,

58:39.733 --> 58:41.213
AND HE STILL DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT I WANT ON MY BURGER.

58:41.256 --> 58:42.780
BEING AN ARMY MOM IS TOUGH,

58:42.823 --> 58:45.565
BUT YOU'VE GOT WHAT
IT TAKES.

58:45.609 --> 58:48.220
- DO YOU REALLY THINK
THEY COULD BE GONE BY JULY?

58:48.263 --> 58:50.875
- NO WAY. NO. LIZ IS JUST
BEING A WORRYWART.

58:50.918 --> 58:52.703
THEY'LL BE HOME
TILL AT LEAST CHRISTMAS.

58:54.400 --> 58:57.664
[cheering]

58:59.448 --> 59:01.363
[kids chattering]

59:11.939 --> 59:13.332
- SORRY, BABE.
I'M LATE AGAIN.

59:13.375 --> 59:15.421
- OH.

59:15.464 --> 59:17.249
I KNEW YOU'D BE HERE.

59:17.292 --> 59:18.642
AND YOU'RE NOT LATE.
THE GAME DIDN'T EVEN START.

59:18.685 --> 59:21.862
- OH, SWEET!

59:21.906 --> 59:23.864
- SO MUCH BETTER.
- YEAH.

59:23.908 --> 59:24.865
[cheers and applause]

59:24.909 --> 59:27.346
- ALL RIGHT, BUD.
GO GET 'EM!

59:27.389 --> 59:29.435
- ALL RIGHT, BLUE, LET'S GO!

59:29.478 --> 59:32.786
- COME ON!

59:32.830 --> 59:33.961
[cheering and applause]

59:34.005 --> 59:36.268
- [dramatic laughing]

59:36.311 --> 59:38.052
THAT WAS A TOUGH ONE
TO FOLLOW.

59:45.451 --> 59:46.583
NICE ONE!

59:46.626 --> 59:48.062
NICE SWING.
NICE CUT, NICE CUT!

59:55.548 --> 59:57.550
NICE HIT, NICE HIT.
NICE CUT, NICE CUT.

59:57.594 --> 59:58.638
THAT'S WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

01:00:05.471 --> 01:00:06.907
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

01:00:30.452 --> 01:00:31.976
YEAH, THAT WAS QUICK.

01:00:32.019 --> 01:00:33.760
THAT WAS A QUICK OUT.
QUICK OUT.

01:00:36.371 --> 01:00:37.938
YEAH, NICE PITCH.
NICE PITCH, MAN.

01:00:42.421 --> 01:00:44.858
[crowd ohs]

01:00:44.902 --> 01:00:47.078
COME ON, THROW IT TO HOME!
THROW IT TO HOME!

01:00:47.121 --> 01:00:48.993
THROW IT HOME!

01:00:51.952 --> 01:00:54.346
[cheering]

01:00:54.389 --> 01:00:56.914
YEAH!
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING!

01:00:56.957 --> 01:00:59.307
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING!

01:01:09.491 --> 01:01:11.972
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING, JARED!
- YEAH!

01:01:12.016 --> 01:01:13.844
- WAY TO BLOCK THE PLATE!

01:01:26.421 --> 01:01:28.685
- AND SO HOW ABOUT BEINGTHANKFUL I WON THE GAME TODAY?

01:01:28.728 --> 01:01:30.034
- DEFINITELY.

01:01:30.077 --> 01:01:31.600
YOU WERE FANTASTIC.

01:01:31.644 --> 01:01:33.124
SEE, I TOLD YOU YOU COULD
PLAY BASEBALL.

01:01:33.167 --> 01:01:35.561
- AND FOR YOU SMILING
SO MUCH NOW.

01:01:35.604 --> 01:01:36.954
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN "NOW"?
I ALWAYS SMILE.

01:01:36.997 --> 01:01:38.695
- NOT LIKE YOU ARE NOW.

01:01:38.738 --> 01:01:40.566
AND THANK YOU, GOD,

01:01:40.609 --> 01:01:42.394
FOR BRINGING VINCENT
INTO OUR LIVES.

01:01:42.437 --> 01:01:43.787
AND THANK YOU FOR ALLOWING
MY MOM TO LOVE AGAIN.

01:01:43.830 --> 01:01:45.484
- [laughing]

01:01:45.527 --> 01:01:47.834
OKAY.

