- DAD.

01:05:49.206 --> 01:05:52.252
- WELL, LET'S SEE
WHAT HE GAVE YOU.

01:05:53.950 --> 01:05:55.342
- OH, A CHARGERS HAT.

01:05:55.386 --> 01:05:57.779
- HOW DID DAD KNOW
OUR TEAM'S THE CHARGERS?

01:05:57.823 --> 01:05:59.477
- UH, MAYBE A LUCKY GUESS.

01:06:01.000 --> 01:06:02.393
FITS PERFECTLY.

01:06:02.436 --> 01:06:03.960
- MM-HMM.
- LOOKS COOL.

01:06:04.003 --> 01:06:05.962
- ALL RIGHT.HERE'S THIS BIG ONE DOWN HERE.

01:06:06.005 --> 01:06:07.789
OH!

01:06:07.833 --> 01:06:09.922
HERE WE GO.

01:06:09.966 --> 01:06:11.750
HERE'S THE CARD.
WHO'S IT FROM?

01:06:11.793 --> 01:06:15.362
- VINCE.

01:06:18.104 --> 01:06:20.411
all: WHOA.

01:06:20.454 --> 01:06:23.283
- COOL.

01:06:23.327 --> 01:06:25.677
- OH, LOOK AT THAT.

01:06:25.720 --> 01:06:27.418
- I GOT IT A LITTLE BIGGER
SO IT'LL FIT YOU NEXT YEAR.

01:06:27.461 --> 01:06:28.636
- THANKS.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

01:06:37.210 --> 01:06:38.690
- GOOD NIGHT.

01:06:38.733 --> 01:06:40.779
I LOVE YOU.
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

01:06:40.822 --> 01:06:44.000
THAT WAS NICE OF GRANDMA.
- WHAT?

01:06:44.043 --> 01:06:45.784
- PRETENDING DAD REMEMBERED
MY BIRTHDAY.

01:06:45.827 --> 01:06:47.829
- DAD DOESN'T SIGN HIS CARDS
"DAD."

01:06:47.873 --> 01:06:49.701
HE JUST PUTS "D."

01:06:49.744 --> 01:06:51.703
- YOU KNOW, YOU LOOK PRETTY COOLIN THAT CATCHER'S MASK.

01:06:51.746 --> 01:06:53.270
YOU THINK YOU MIGHT BEA PROFESSIONAL BASEBALL PLAYER?

01:06:53.313 --> 01:06:55.446
- MAYBE.

01:06:55.489 --> 01:06:57.317
I KINDA WANT TO BE A SOLDIER.

01:06:57.361 --> 01:06:59.711
WOULD YOU MIND?

01:06:59.754 --> 01:07:02.105
- WELL, I DON'T KNOW.
I WOULD MISS YOU.

01:07:02.148 --> 01:07:03.932
BUT WE HAVE A FEW YEARS BEFOREWE HAVE TO THINK ABOUT THAT.

01:07:03.976 --> 01:07:06.370
WE'LL JUMP OFF THAT BRIDGE
WHEN WE GET TO IT.

01:07:06.413 --> 01:07:07.980
- WHAT'S UP?

01:07:08.024 --> 01:07:09.460
- NOTHING.
I LOVE YOU.

01:07:09.503 --> 01:07:10.983
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

01:07:11.027 --> 01:07:12.202
- GOOD NIGHT.

01:07:15.857 --> 01:07:17.468
HEY.
- HOW'S HE DOING?

01:07:17.511 --> 01:07:20.340
- HE IS FALLING ASLEEPWITH A SMILE FROM EAR TO EAR.

01:07:20.384 --> 01:07:22.473
- BIRTHDAY WAS A BIG DAY.

01:07:22.516 --> 01:07:26.259
- EXACTLY WHEN DID YOU BUY
THAT CATCHER'S MASK?

01:07:26.303 --> 01:07:27.782
- A FEW WEEKS AGO.

01:07:27.826 --> 01:07:29.958
- THAT'S AMAZING.

01:07:30.002 --> 01:07:32.309
YOU REMEMBERED HIS BIRTHDAY
A FEW WEEKS AGO

01:07:32.352 --> 01:07:34.354
AND HIS OWN FATHER COULDN'T EVENREMEMBER TO CALL HIM TODAY.

01:07:38.315 --> 01:07:39.142
- HOW'S WORK GOING?

01:07:39.185 --> 01:07:41.013
- OH, DON'T ASK.

01:07:41.057 --> 01:07:44.277
THE EASIER THE SOFTWARE BECOMESTHE MORE BORED I GET.

01:07:44.321 --> 01:07:45.887
- SO WHY KEEP DOING IT?

01:07:45.931 --> 01:07:50.849
- WELL, JARED'S GOT TO EAT.
SO DO I.

01:07:50.892 --> 01:07:53.895
- YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T JUST QUITBASEBALL

01:07:53.939 --> 01:07:55.984
'CAUSE I COULDN'T HIT
A CURVE BALL.

01:07:56.028 --> 01:07:57.986
I MEAN, EVEN IF I WOULD'VE MADETHE MAJORS,

01:07:58.030 --> 01:08:00.989
MOST PLAYERS DON'T LAST
PAST FOUR YEARS.

01:08:01.033 --> 01:08:03.862
COURSE I WOULD'VE BEEN RICH.

01:08:03.905 --> 01:08:06.473
BUT WHAT'S THAT REALLY GOING
TO GET ME?

01:08:06.517 --> 01:08:08.084
WHAT WOULD I DO WITH THE RESTOF MY LIFE?

01:08:08.127 --> 01:08:10.956
LIVE OFF THE MEMORIES?

01:08:10.999 --> 01:08:12.436
SEE, THAT'S WHAT I GET OUT OFTHE ARMY.

01:08:12.479 --> 01:08:16.353
A LIFETIME OF DOING
WHAT I LOVE TO DO.

01:08:16.395 --> 01:08:18.310
YOU DESERVE THAT, DANA.

01:08:18.354 --> 01:08:21.009
WASN'T THE WHOLE POINT OF YOUMOVING IN HERE WITH LOUISE

01:08:21.053 --> 01:08:22.272
SO YOU COULD FIND OUT
WHAT YOU WANT TO DO

01:08:22.314 --> 01:08:24.317
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE?

01:08:24.361 --> 01:08:27.363
- YEAH, I--
I SUPPOSE IT WAS.

01:08:27.407 --> 01:08:29.408
- OKAY, WELL, IF NOT DRAFTING,WHAT?

01:08:29.453 --> 01:08:33.935
- WHEN I WAS A LITTLE GIRL,
I WANTED TO BE AN ARCHITECT.

01:08:33.979 --> 01:08:37.024
YOU KNOW, DESIGN BEAUTIFUL HOMESFOR PEOPLE.

01:08:37.069 --> 01:08:40.116
BUT DRAFTING WAS THE BEST
PLAN "B" AVAILABLE.

01:08:40.158 --> 01:08:44.032
- WELL, I SAY GO BACK
TO PLAN "A" THEN.

01:08:44.076 --> 01:08:46.470
YOU KNOW, GO BACK TO SCHOOL.
BECOME AN ARCHITECT.

01:08:46.513 --> 01:08:49.386
THEY HAVE NIGHT SCHOOL,
THEY HAVE PART-TIME.

01:08:49.429 --> 01:08:50.822
WHATEVER IT TAKES.

01:08:50.865 --> 01:08:53.433
AND WHERE THERE'S A WILL...

01:08:53.477 --> 01:08:57.045
WE'RE ONLY ON THIS EARTH
ONCE SO...

01:08:57.089 --> 01:08:59.178
WE MIGHT AS WELL DO WHAT GOD
PUT US HERE TO DO, RIGHT?

01:09:01.441 --> 01:09:02.616
- THANK YOU.

01:09:09.014 --> 01:09:12.452
OKAY, I'M GONNA GO.
- ALL RIGHT, DANA.

01:09:12.496 --> 01:09:16.456
GOOD NIGHT.
- GOOD NIGHT.

01:09:20.504 --> 01:09:22.462
- DID VINCE LEAVE?
- YES.

01:09:22.506 --> 01:09:25.944
MOM, WHAT WOULD THINK ABOUT MEGOING TO NIGHT SCHOOL?

01:09:25.987 --> 01:09:27.598
- TO DO WHAT?
- ARCHITECTURE.

01:09:27.640 --> 01:09:30.035
- [gasp]

01:09:30.078 --> 01:09:31.470
IT'S SOMETHING YOU'VE ALWAYS
WANTED TO DO.

01:09:31.515 --> 01:09:33.037
- I WOULD KEEP MY DAY JOB,

01:09:33.081 --> 01:09:34.996
BUT WOULD NEED HELP WITH JAREDAT NIGHT,

01:09:35.040 --> 01:09:37.085
AND IT MIGHT MEAN US LIVING HERELONGER THAN WE THOUGHT.

01:09:37.129 --> 01:09:38.609
IS THAT OKAY?

01:09:38.652 --> 01:09:40.437
- OOH.
I DON'T KNOW.

01:09:40.479 --> 01:09:46.051
THE WAY I SEE IT,
I WIN ON ALL FRONTS.

01:09:46.094 --> 01:09:48.618
- THANK YOU!
OH, THANK YOU.

01:09:48.662 --> 01:09:49.968
I'M EXCITED.
- YOU'LL DO GREAT.

01:09:50.011 --> 01:09:53.058
- OH, I KNOW.
[sigh]

01:09:53.100 --> 01:09:54.581
- FINALLY, SERGEANTS,

01:09:54.625 --> 01:09:57.497
AN ORDER I KNOW YOU'VE ALL BEENLOOKING FORWARD TO,

01:09:57.541 --> 01:09:59.891
AS THE FIRST OF A DEPLOYMENT
READINESS ASSESSMENT...

01:09:59.934 --> 01:10:01.414
- WE'RE SHIPPING OUT.
- I CAN'T BELIEVE.

01:10:01.458 --> 01:10:04.243
- THE COLONEL HAS ORDERED
THAT WE DO A FULL INVENTORY

01:10:04.287 --> 01:10:07.028
OF ALL EQUIPMENT, STORES,
UNIFORMS, ET CETERA.

01:10:07.072 --> 01:10:08.465
IF IT BREATHES, SALUTE IT.

01:10:08.508 --> 01:10:10.423
IF IT DOESN'T,
PUT IT ON THE LIST.

01:10:10.467 --> 01:10:12.077
WHAT IS IT, SERGEANT?

01:10:12.120 --> 01:10:14.035
- ANY IDEA WHEN WE'RE SHIPPINGOUT, SERGEANT MAJOR?

01:10:14.079 --> 01:10:15.211
- SERGEANTS, ALL I KNOW IS
THE COMMANDER HAS REQUESTED

01:10:15.254 --> 01:10:16.647
A FULL D.R.A.

01:10:16.690 --> 01:10:18.431
WHY, WHEN, WHERE, AND EVEN IFWE'RE GOING,

01:10:18.475 --> 01:10:22.261
YOU'LL KNOW WHEN I KNOW.

01:10:26.483 --> 01:10:27.440
- DUDE, YOUR MOVE.
COME ON.

01:10:27.484 --> 01:10:30.182
- OH, I'M SORRY, BUD.

01:10:30.226 --> 01:10:31.662
UH, LET'S SEE.

01:10:31.705 --> 01:10:34.055
THERE YOU GO.

01:10:34.099 --> 01:10:34.969
- ARE YOU SURE YOU WANNA
DO THAT?

01:10:35.013 --> 01:10:37.668
- YEAH.
- OKAY.

01:10:37.711 --> 01:10:40.236
KING ME.

01:10:40.279 --> 01:10:44.675
- NICE MOVE, BUD.
- THANKS.

01:10:44.718 --> 01:10:45.719
- [sigh]

01:10:48.113 --> 01:10:50.420
[footsteps]

01:10:53.727 --> 01:10:55.512
- ARE YOU OKAY?

01:10:55.555 --> 01:10:56.687
YOU'VE BEEN SOMEWHERE ELSE
ALL EVENING.

01:10:56.730 --> 01:10:58.602
- OH, YEAH.

01:10:58.645 --> 01:11:01.082
I'M SORRY.
I'M JUST--

01:11:01.126 --> 01:11:04.477
I'M JUST TIRED,
THAT'S ALL.

01:11:04.521 --> 01:11:07.001
WOULD YOU MIND IF I CALLED ITAN EARLY NIGHT TONIGHT?

01:11:07.045 --> 01:11:08.438
- GO HOME AND GET SOME SLEEP.

01:11:08.481 --> 01:11:09.656
- THANKS.

01:11:17.664 --> 01:11:18.665
- GOOD NIGHT.
- GOOD NIGHT.

01:11:27.108 --> 01:11:29.720
WE'RE DOING OUR D.R.A.

01:11:29.763 --> 01:11:33.158
THAT'S DEPLOYMENT READINESS
ASSESSMENT.

01:11:33.201 --> 01:11:35.116
I'M BEING REDEPLOYED.

01:11:35.160 --> 01:11:37.554
- ISN'T THAT SOONER
THAN YOU EXPECTED?

01:11:37.597 --> 01:11:39.120
- YEAH.

01:11:39.164 --> 01:11:40.992
- WHEN DO YOU LEAVE?

01:11:43.647 --> 01:11:47.999
- THEY HAVEN'T TOLD US YET.

01:12:06.278 --> 01:12:08.324
- GOOD NIGHT.

01:12:08.367 --> 01:12:10.151
I LOVE YOU.

01:12:10.195 --> 01:12:13.024
- MOM?

01:12:13.067 --> 01:12:14.199
- HEY, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE ASLEEP.

01:12:14.242 --> 01:12:15.722
- ARE YOU OKAY?

01:12:15.766 --> 01:12:18.159
YOU SOUND KINDA SAD.
- I DO?

01:12:18.203 --> 01:12:21.380
I'M SORRY.

01:12:21.424 --> 01:12:25.602
VINCE'S UNIT IS GETTING READYTO SHIP OUT AGAIN.

01:12:25.645 --> 01:12:27.081
- WHEN?

01:12:27.125 --> 01:12:28.779
- HE DOESN'T KNOW YET.

01:12:28.822 --> 01:12:30.607
- I'LL MISS HIM.

01:12:30.650 --> 01:12:32.609
- ME TOO.

01:12:32.652 --> 01:12:35.307
- WHAT'LL HAPPEN?

01:12:35.351 --> 01:12:37.135
- WELL, YOU'LL WRITE EACH OTHER.

01:12:37.178 --> 01:12:40.747
- NO, WHAT'LL HAPPEN...
TO YOU AND HIM?

01:12:42.662 --> 01:12:43.837
- I DON'T KNOW.

01:12:47.406 --> 01:12:48.494
GOOD NIGHT.

01:12:48.538 --> 01:12:51.062
- GOOD NIGHT.

01:12:55.458 --> 01:12:59.113
- BOY, YOU'VE GOTTA BE STRONG
TO BE A SOLDIER'S WIFE.

01:12:59.157 --> 01:13:01.377
- WHAT BROUGHT THAT ON?

01:13:01.420 --> 01:13:03.291
VINCE HASN'T ASKED YOU
TO MARRY HIM HAS HE?

01:13:03.335 --> 01:13:05.772
- [laughing]
NO.

01:13:05.816 --> 01:13:09.210
I WAS JUST THINKING.
- UH-HUH.

01:13:09.254 --> 01:13:12.300
- THEY'RE GETTING READY
TO GO OVERSEAS AGAIN SOON.

01:13:12.344 --> 01:13:15.216
- REALLY?

01:13:15.260 --> 01:13:17.262
I THOUGHT THEY WERE STAYING
UNTIL CHRISTMAS.

01:13:17.305 --> 01:13:18.698
- MM.

01:13:18.742 --> 01:13:20.439
- WHAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN
TO THE TWO OF YOU?

01:13:20.483 --> 01:13:21.658
- WELL, WE ALWAYS SAID
WE WOULD CROSS THAT BRIDGE

01:13:21.701 --> 01:13:23.529
WHEN WE CAME TO IT.

01:13:23.573 --> 01:13:25.662
THE TRUTH IS IT'S ALWAYS BEENTHERE RIGHT IN FRONT OF US

01:13:25.705 --> 01:13:27.446
LIKE A TIME LIMIT.

01:13:27.490 --> 01:13:31.842
JUST KEPT US FROM MAKING ANY
OTHER PERMANENT DECISIONS.

01:13:31.885 --> 01:13:33.670
BUT...

01:13:33.713 --> 01:13:36.412
NOW THAT BRIDGE--WELL, WE'RE
GETTING READY TO CROSS IT.

01:13:36.455 --> 01:13:37.413
- WHAT DO YOU WANT TO HAPPEN?

01:13:37.456 --> 01:13:40.154
- I DON'T KNOW, MOM.

01:13:40.198 --> 01:13:44.115
VINCE'S WIFE LEFT HIM
WHEN HE WAS OVERSEAS.

01:13:44.158 --> 01:13:45.638
HE WAS THOUSANDS OF MILES AWAYAND THE WOMAN HE LOVED

01:13:45.682 --> 01:13:47.205
RAN OFF WITH SOMEBODY ELSE

01:13:47.248 --> 01:13:49.816
AND THERE WASN'T ANYTHING
HE COULD DO ABOUT IT.

01:13:49.860 --> 01:13:51.427
SO NO MATTER HOW WE FEEL
ABOUT EACH OTHER,

01:13:51.470 --> 01:13:56.606
I JUST DON'T THINK HE'LL RISKTHAT HAPPENING AGAIN.

01:13:56.649 --> 01:13:58.172
I'LL MISS HIM.

01:13:58.216 --> 01:13:59.522
- DO YOU LOVE HIM?

